# BROWSER-notifications.md - Substack Notification & Reply Detection Patterns

## SS 1. Extract Notifications

Page: `https://substack.com/activity` (embed 3s wait in evaluate)

Substack calls notifications "Activity". Tabs: All, Replies, Restacks. Only process "Replies" tab items.

🚨 **Dedup key = URL + text snippet.** Substack does NOT expose unique per-comment URLs on the activity page. Multiple replies on the same thread share the same note URL. The `snippet` field (first 30 chars of reply body) distinguishes them.

🚨 **"Replied to your note" notifications have NO post URL in the DOM** — only the author profile link. When a notification has `isReply=true` but no `/note/` or `/p/` link, the agent must click the row to discover the URL, then navigate back to `/activity` before continuing extraction. See Step 2 below.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var tabs = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var repliesTab = tabs.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Replies'); if (repliesTab) { repliesTab.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); } if (document.body.innerText.includes(\"don't have any activity\")) { return { count: 0, items: [], empty: true }; } var rows = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(\"[class*='linkRow']\")); var seen = new Set(); var items = []; for (var row of rows) { var text = row.innerText || ''; var isReply = /replied|commented|response/i.test(text); if (!isReply) continue; var author = text.split(String.fromCharCode(10))[0] || ''; if (/{{name}}|{{handle}}/i.test(author)) continue; var link = Array.from(row.querySelectorAll('a[href]')).find(a => { var h = a.href || ''; return h.includes('/note/') || h.includes('/p/') || h.includes('/comment/'); }); if (!link) continue; var url = link.href.split('?')[0]; var lines = text.split(String.fromCharCode(10)).filter(l => l.trim()); var snippet = ''; for (var i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) { var line = lines[i].trim(); if (line.length > 20 && !/replied|commented|liked|your comment on/i.test(line) && !/^\\d+[hmd]$/.test(line)) { snippet = line.slice(0, 30); break; } } var key = url + '|' + snippet; if (seen.has(key)) continue; seen.add(key); items.push({ type: 'reply', author: author.slice(0, 40), postUrl: url, snippet: snippet, rowIndex: Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(\"[class*='linkRow']\")).indexOf(row), needsClick: !url }); if (items.length >= 10) break; } return { count: items.length, items }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

---

## SS 1b. Resolve Missing URLs (for "replied to your note" notifications)

🚨 **Only needed for items where `needsClick: true`** (no `/note/` or `/p/` link found in DOM).

For each item with `needsClick: true`:
1. Click the notification row by index to navigate to the note
2. Read `window.location.href` — this gives the note URL (e.g. `/@author/note/c-XXXXXXX`)
3. Navigate back to `https://substack.com/activity` and re-click "Replies" tab
4. Store the discovered URL in the item's `postUrl`

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var rows = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(\"[class*='linkRow']\")); var targetRow = rows[ROW_INDEX_PLACEHOLDER]; if (!targetRow) return { error: 'row not found at index' }; var clickable = targetRow.querySelector(\"[class*='isClickable']\") || targetRow; clickable.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); return { url: window.location.href }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

After getting the URL, navigate back:
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"https://substack.com/activity"}' 2>&1
```
Wait 3s, click "Replies" tab again.

🚨 **Do this BEFORE the grep pre-check** — items need URLs for dedup to work.

---

## SS 2. Check Already Replied

Use tracking file dedup (grep pre-check) as primary method. Browser-based checks are unreliable for reply detection.

🚨 **Dedup key includes snippet** — same URL can have multiple replies from the same author. The snippet (first 30 chars of reply body) makes each entry unique.

**Tracking file format:**
```
reply|{author}|{url}|{snippet}|{ISO_TIMESTAMP}
```

**Grep check** — use `{url}|{first 15 chars of snippet}` for matching (shorter = tolerant of length variations):
```bash
grep -qF "{url}|{snippet_first_15_chars}" memory/replied_notifications_substack.txt && echo "SKIP" || echo "OK"
```

**Batch check (preferred):**
```bash
printf '%s\n' "{url1}|{snippet1_15chars}" "{url2}|{snippet2_15chars}" ... | while read line; do grep -qF "$line" memory/replied_notifications_substack.txt && echo "SKIP: $line" || echo "NEW: $line"; done
```

🚨 **Tracking file stores full 30-char snippet.** Grep uses first 15 chars as substring match (`-F` fixed string). This handles minor variations in snippet length between extraction runs.
